<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--EarringArgument     03-17 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Earring Argument,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>After Dispute with Mother, Boy Tells Police About Marijuana Stash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAFAYETTE, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy who was angry because
his mother refused to allow him to have an ear pierced called police
and told them where to find eight pounds of marijuana hidden in his
home.
   Police searched the home Tuesday night and found 11 packages
containing marijuana with an estimated street value of $15,000.
   Police on Thursday said a warrant for the father's arrest was
being drafted, charging possession and distribution of marijuana.
   ``There was a dispute over him (the boy) getting a pierced ear,''
said police Lt. Brad Wiesley. ``His mother was not happy about it.
They just had a mother-son argument.''
   After the dispute, the boy called police from a nearby shopping
center.
   ``He told us about what was in the house,'' Wiesley said. ``He
wasn't too happy that there was marijuana in the house.''
   The boy, one of four children in the home, was taken into
protective custody.
</TEXT>
