<HEAD>Rain Along Pacific Coast; Snow Extends East From Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain fell along the northern Pacific Coast today while snow
settled across the northern Rockies, upper Missouri Valley, South
Dakota and southern Minnesota, as well as lower Michigan.
   Advisories for snow this morning were posted for Oregon's Cascade
Range and Siskiyous, Lake Tahoe in western Nevada, much of Idaho,
northern Utah, western Wyoming, and through south-central Montana.
   Advisories for snow and blowing snow today were up for parts of
South Dakota and Wisconsin, and a winter storm watch for southern
Minnesota.
   A high-wind advisory continued for southeast California and a
high-wind watch for northeast Colorado.
   By Thursday evening, a storm had dumped more than a foot of snow
in the higher elevations of the Tahoe Valley, with 6 to 10 inches
near lake level.
   Winds gusted to 55 mph at Las Vegas during the evening, 57 mph at
Cedar City, Utah, and 59 mph at Milford, Utah, as well as 60 mph at
Fort Carson, Colo., and Salt Lake City.
   The nation's high temperature Thursday was 90 degrees at Ocala,
Fla.
   Today's forecast called for snow from the Great Lakes across the
upper Mississippi Valley and the northern Plains to the northern
Rockies; rain in the Pacific Northwest and northern California;
showers and thunderstorms scattered in northern Texas, Oklahoma and
Arkansas; strong, gusty winds in the central Rockies.
   Predicted highs: teens and 20s from western Montana across the
Dakotas and the upper Mississippi Valley to northern parts of the
upper Great Lakes; 30s and 40s across the northern Rockies, northern
Nebraska, much of Iowa, southern parts of the upper Great Lakes, and
the lower Great Lakes to northern New England; 70s and 80s from the
desert Southwest across the southern Rockies, the southern Plains,
Kansas, the lower Mississippi Valley, the Gulf Coast region and the
Tennessee Valley to the southern Atlantic Coast and Florida.
   The rest of the nation will generally have highs in the 50s and
60s.
   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 15 degrees
below zero at Hibbing, Minn., to 74 degrees at St. Petersburg, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 55 fair; Boston 40 fair; Buffalo 27 snow;
Charleston, S.C., 57 cloudy; Cincinnati 41 fair; Cleveland 33 partly
cloudy; Detroit 34 cloudy; Miami 67 fair; New York 40 fair;
Philadelphia 38 fair; Pittsburgh 38 fair; Portland, Maine, 37 fair;
Washington 42 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 7 fair; Chicago 33 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
65 fair; Denver 27 fair; Des Moines 23 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
37 fair; Kansas City 39 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 8 snow;
Nashville 39 fair; New Orleans 66 foggy; St. Louis 50 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 50 fair; Anchorage 20 fair; Las Vegas 55 fair;
Los Angeles 52 fair; Phoenix 67 partly cloudy; Salt Lake City 38
fair; San Diego 57 cloudy; San Francisco 50 fair; Seattle 38 partly
cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 25 windy; Toronto 23 snow.
