<SECOND>PM-Israel-Arson,0331</SECOND>
<HEAD>Arsonist Sets Fire To Building Where Journalist, Lawmaker Stay</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities today blamed an underground group of
Jewish militants for arson attacks on the homes of a journalist and
a relative of a left-wing legislator.
   Both the columnist and the lawmaker have angered Jewish militants
because they talked to supporters of the Palestine Liberation
Organization.
   No one was reported injured in the Thursday night attacks, which
occurred at the same apartment building in Jerusalem.
   Police said a Jewish underground group that claimed
responsibility for two similar arson attacks last month was
responsible for the latest incidents.
   An arsonist set fire to the Jerusalem apartment doors of Dan
Margalit, a columnist for the Ha'aretz newspaper and a television
show host.
   At about the same time, an arsonist started a fire against a door
at the residence of Omer Shiloni, nephew of Knesset member Yair
Tsaban.
   It appeared the arsonist may have mistaken the apartment for that
of Tsaban's son, Dror, who also lives in the building. The lawmaker
stays there when he is in the city.
   An anonymous telephone caller contacted the mass-circulation
newspaper Yediot Ahronot and said the attacks were politically
motivated.
   He said his group, which he did not identify, targeted ``the
apartments of Dan Margalit and Yair Tsaban _ their names should be
erased from the face of the earth _ because Margalit invited Faisal
Husseini to appear on television and Tsaban met with the PLO
overseas.''
   Tsaban, whose left-wing Mapam party calls for talks with the PLO,
has participated in several international conferences alongside PLO
officials. Margalit had Husseini, a pro-PLO leader in the occupied
territories, on his TV show several weeks ago.
   Police attributed the attacks to an underground group called the
Sicarites after a Jewish movement that operated in Roman times. The
ancient Sicarites named themselves after ``sica'' daggers that they
carried to murder Jews who collaborated with Rome.
