<HEAD>One Killed, One Injured In Explosives Factory Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AVLONA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A blast tore through a chemical laboratory
Friday, killing one man, wounding another and spraying acid 150
feet, police said.
   A police spokesman said employee Sotiris Meletiou, 25, was killed
instantly while his partner Theodoros Spanoudis, 23, was seriously
injured when the explosion ripped through the Atlas Corp. laboratory.
   Spanoudis was hospitalized with burns over most of his body and
was listed in critical condition, he said. The two men were alone
when the explosion occured, said the spokesman, speaking on
condition of anonymity.
   ``We don't know why it happened, but the blast demolished the
first floor of the three-story building,'' he said. The spokesman
said ``some kind of acid'' sprayed over a 150-foot area.
   Avlona is a village 26 miles north of Athens.
