<HEAD>Bridge Collapses, Killing Four, Injuring 157</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A metal footbridge collapsed Friday under
the weight of several hundred people in the eastern suburb of
El-Harrach, causing four deaths and 157 injuries, state-run
television reported.
   The television newscast blamed the disaster on the poor condition
of the bridge, which it said was about 70 years old.
