<HEAD>Actors Unions Reach Early Contract Settlement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The two largest actors unions have reached a
tentative contract settlement with television and film producers,
officials said Friday.
   Mark Locher, a spokesman for the 70,000-member Screen Actors
Guild, said negotiators for SAG and the 68,000-member American
Federation of Television and Radio Artists ``were polishing the
final contract language.''
