<FIRST>r a AM-Shuttle-Networks     03-17 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Shuttle-Networks,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shuttle Landing To Interrupt Some Saturday Morning Cartoons</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Space Shuttle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPACE CENTER, Houston (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC's Saturday morning cartoon
lineup will be interrupted by the space shuttle Discovery's landing,
but the network's coverage will be geared for the younger audience,
a spokeswoman said.
   The network will pre-empt its ``Smurfs'' cartoon series to air
the shuttle's touchdown, which is scheduled for 6:35 a.m. PST, NBC
spokeswoman Helen Manasian said Friday.
   The anticipated younger audience prompted NBC to ``target the
coverage to appeal to kids,'' Ms. Manasian said. Vocabulary,
graphics and discussions will ``be geared for kids.''
   The coverage, which will last about 10 minutes, will be anchored
by Connie Chung. Astronaut George ``Pinky'' Nelson will be at the
Johnson Space Center to help with commentary, Ms. Manasian said.
   CBS also will interrupt its cartoon lineup with the shuttle
landing, but it plans no special changes in its coverage for the
younger audience. ABC will be on stand-by for live coverage, but it
has no plans to pre-empt its program.
</TEXT>
