<HEAD>Dollar Calm After Advancing Against Yen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar advanced against the Japanese yen
but was mixed in calm European trading this morning as dealers
awaited Washington's announcement of the producer price index.
   Gold was steady after falling in Hong Kong. ``There is no sense
of direction,'' said one precious metals trader in London.
   ``The dollar's strength is a continuation of a worldwide trend
reflecting better-than-expected trade reports of the United States
Wednesday,'' said a trader for a major U.S. bank in Tokyo.
   In Tokyo, where trading ends before Europe's business day begins,
the dollar rose 0.34 Japanese yen to a closing 131.07 yen. Later, in
London, it rose to 131.10 yen.
